description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a highly motivated and dynamic individual that drives for continuous service improvement?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you caring, compassionate and committed to providing the best care for patients?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, an exciting opportunity has arisen Bournville Ward for a Junior Charge Nurse/Sister at University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are passionate and proud about delivering excellent patient care that is evidenced and research based.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is suitably qualified and experienced within Medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ongoing training, development and support will be offered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have a motivation and determination to succeed; be able to demonstrate sound clinical knowledge with a special interest in nursing leadership and education, and should have the ability to work autonomously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be flexible and resourceful as you help lead and develop the ward to provide excellent nursing care.&lt;/p&gt;
